Recurssion is a process in which a function/meathod calls itself continously.
Recurssion make the code compact but complicated to understand

Ex: Adding 2 number series using recurssion

class Add{
    public static int add(int n){
        if(n==0){
            return 0;
        }else{
            return n + add(n-1);
        }
    }
    public static void main(String [] args){
        int sum = add(10);
        System.out.println(sum);
    }
}
